      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAWBOURNE LADY (4) looks close to another win after finishing third from Box 5 last time (30.89) at this track. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Overdue and gets her chance. MAXIMUM DAMAGE (6) was sent out long odds last time but rocketed out of the boxes with a fast early sectional and gave a sight before being swallowed up late, finishing a 3 length second (25.97) over 460m at Geelong. Has good early speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Hard to beat again. SCRUTINISE (1) boasts a strong record this journey here with two wins and two minors from six tries. In the money last time at Temora (26.01) in a Grade 4/5, finishing a 1.5 lengths third. Looks a key chance on best figures. HERO BLUES (2) returns from a seven weeks layoff in a suitable contest.",
